And these cucumbers
were a little smaller.

00:49:29.490 --> 00:49:30.590
You can see, though.

00:49:30.590 --> 00:49:33.590
They look like real pickles, right?

00:49:33.590 --> 00:49:34.450
Pretty cool.

00:49:34.450 --> 00:49:36.430
It's so easy.

00:49:36.430 --> 00:49:40.090
You're going to want to start your own
fermentation program in your house.

00:49:45.860 --> 00:49:51.340
OK, we're going to cheat a little bit,
because I'm going to finish this up.

00:49:51.340 --> 00:49:54.360
You can see the difference in
the color and what happens.

00:49:54.360 --> 00:49:56.200
And clearly, that's acid.

00:49:56.200 --> 00:50:02.570
And all that is salt, peppercorns,
and garlic, and water.

00:50:02.570 --> 00:50:06.196
It's all the acid from the fermentation.

00:50:18.281 --> 00:50:19.780
We used up all our bowls, didn't we?

00:50:25.470 --> 00:50:26.740
Here, I'm going to use this.

00:50:38.170 --> 00:50:41.960
So I'm going to put my yogurt in here.

00:50:51.180 --> 00:50:52.260
Add a little bit of milk.

00:51:15.214 --> 00:51:18.220
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE].

00:51:18.220 --> 00:51:21.494
JODY ADAMS: To temper it a little bit.

00:51:41.640 --> 00:51:44.850
It's to temper it, to
even out the temperature.

00:52:24.470 --> 00:52:28.470
This milk is way too hot.

